Travellers who will be going to high transmission areas in the country and outside, are warned to take precautions against being bitten by mosquitoes. Speaking for the institute, Professor Lucille Blumberg advises that those who have been in high-risk malaria areas and have developed a fever, should get tested and start treatment immediately. Malaria symptoms include fever, flu-like symptoms, cold shivers, hot sweats, headache as well as muscle pain. Blumberg explains furtherâ€¦